						Venture consultancy advising early-stage DeFi and fintech founders.
						Three portfolio companies including <a href="https://gammaswap.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><b>Gammaswap</b></a>
						and <a href="https://www.codex.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><b>Codex</b></a>.
						Influenced <b>$4M+ in aggregate fundraising</b> through advisory work and warm introductions.
					</li>
				</ul>

				<div class="role">
					<button class="role-trigger" data-window-trigger="gmx" aria-haspopup="dialog">
						<b>GMX</b> — <em>Founding Team · Growth &amp; Partnerships</em>
					</button>
					<div class="dates">Dec 2020 – 2023</div>
				</div>
				<ul>
					<li>
						Three-person founding team. Top DeFi revenue generator during my tenure.
						Co-led institutional partnerships and capital formation; personally sourced
						<b>$20M+ in cumulative capital deployments</b>.
					</li>
					<li>
						Closed and co-closed strategic partnerships with <Sidenote id="chainlink" term="Chainlink"><em>[PLACEHOLDER — 50 words]</em> The Chainlink BUILD programme integration gave us oracle pricing for the entire perpetuals book. Negotiated the grant component and the keeper-network configuration with Chainlink Labs.</Sidenote>, <Sidenote id="avalanche" term="Avalanche"><em>[PLACEHOLDER — 50 words]</em> The Avalanche Rush deployment incentive was one of the largest external capital injections into GMX, and the cross-chain expansion roughly doubled our TVL within two months.</Sidenote>, and <Sidenote id="frax" term="Frax"><em>[PLACEHOLDER — 50 words]</em> The Frax integration brought frxETH liquidity into GLP and gave us a stablecoin alternative to USDC. Co-designed the parameters with the Frax core team.</Sidenote>, plus three smaller protocol integrations. Coordinated the <HoverCard term="Gambit → GMX rebrand">
							<span class="hc-p">The rebrand wasn't a marketing exercise; it was a chain migration from BSC (Gambit) to Arbitrum and Avalanche (GMX), with the partner network lined up to launch alongside.</span>
							<span class="hc-p"><em>[PLACEHOLDER — replace with 150–200 word account: why the rebrand was technically necessary, your specific role, timeline coordination across partners.]</em></span>
						</HoverCard> and organised outreach to future partners.
					</li>
					<li>
						Built and led the institutional and community channels: <b>5,000+ Telegram members</b> and direct relationships with eight-figure liquidity providers.
					</li>
				</ul>

				<div class="role">
					<button class="role-trigger" data-window-trigger="effie" aria-haspopup="dialog">
						<b>Effie Perine LTD.</b> — <em>Operations &amp; Client Relations</em>
					</button>
					<div class="dates">2019 – 2020</div>
				</div>
				<ul>
					<li>
						Managed financial accounts and operational administration for a private art dealership specialising in Old Master Pictures; annual transaction volumes in the £500K–£2.5M+ range.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</Collapsible>

			<Collapsible title="Current AI Deployments">
				<ul>
					<li>
						<HoverCard term="Pawlymarket">
							<span class="hc-p">Live scraper and statistical-arbitrage layer over prediction markets. Reads order books across Kalshi, Polymarket, and smaller venues; identifies systematic mispricings; surfaces them as actionable calls.</span>
							<span class="hc-p"><em>[PLACEHOLDER — replace with 150 words on engineering architecture (scrape-aggregator, statistical model layer, P&amp;L attribution), revenue trajectory, lessons learned. Embed dashboard screenshot.]</em></span>
							<span class="hc-p further-reading">→ <a href="https://pawlymarket.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">pawlymarket.com</a></span>
						</HoverCard> — live scraper and data aggregator using statistical models to identify market inefficiencies. <b>$50K ARR</b> within two months of launch. <a href="https://pawlymarket.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">pawlymarket.com</a>.
					</li>
					<li>
						<Sidenote id="vinted" term="Vinted-to-Depop reselling agent"><em>[PLACEHOLDER — 75 words]</em> An end-to-end autonomous fashion-arbitrage agent operating across Vinted and Depop. Driven by Claude through a Telegram interface; sources items, calculates margins, lists, fulfills.</Sidenote> — end-to-end autonomous fashion-arbitrage agent operated via Telegram.
					</li>
					<li>
						<Sidenote id="booking" term="Intelligent booking system"><em>[PLACEHOLDER — 50 words]</em> Claude-powered scheduler for a small local business. Takes class bookings, reschedules around capacity constraints, and organises future classes from predicted demand.</Sidenote> — Claude-powered agentic scheduler for a small local business; takes class bookings and organises future classes based on predicted demand.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</Collapsible>

			<Collapsible title="Education">
				<p>
					<b>BSc Chemistry</b>, <em><Sidenote id="manchester" term="University of Manchester"><em>[PLACEHOLDER — 75 words]</em> The interesting work didn't happen in the lab. It happened in the basement of a friend's house in Fallowfield, where I ran a trading-bot operation arbitraging Steam item markets through several account-pool generations. First time I shipped code that made money while I slept.</Sidenote></em>, 2018.
				</p>
			</Collapsible>

			<Collapsible title="Skills">
				<p class="skills">
					Consultative selling to technical buyers · enterprise negotiation · founder-network leverage · community-led growth · technical product evangelism · venture capital · startup operations · risk management · marketing outreach · financial modelling · Claude API · Claude Code · prompt engineering · agentic workflows · <Sidenote id="mcp" term="MCP"><em>[PLACEHOLDER — 50 words]</em> Model Context Protocol changed my development process the day it shipped. The model–tool boundary becoming a clean protocol is the kind of small, correct architectural decision that compounds.</Sidenote> · Python · JavaScript
				</p>
			</Collapsible>
		</div>

		<footer class="cv-footer">
			<a href="mailto:paul.ashot@icloud.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">paul.ashot@icloud.com</a> ·
			@supersonicsines ·
			<a href="/Paul_Diaz_Ashot_CV.pdf" download target="_blank" rel="noopener">Download CV (PDF)</a>
		</footer>
	</main>

